1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:57,720
You should hurry before the boat
goes deeper into the Lost Woods!

3
00:01:54,090 --> 00:02:00,480
The Village Hidden in the Clouds

4
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:58,640
Hey!

5
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:02,100
We gotta go after the boat
before it gets away!

6
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:06,690
It'll be a disaster if we
lose it in this forest!

7
00:02:06,690 --> 00:02:07,940
Wait, Usopp!

8
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:10,070
The same can be said
if we get separated!

9
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:11,570
Luffy! What about you?!

10
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:13,490
You guys stop the boat!

11
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:16,070
I'll take care of the ball guy!

12
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,240
In your dreams!

13
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:21,200
I'm filled with bliss and pride!

14
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:26,250
I guess we do need someone
to stop that Daruma.

15
00:02:26,670 --> 00:02:28,170
Don't do anything reckless!

16
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:30,000
He's got some weird powers!

17
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,220
We'll return once we stop the boat!

18
00:02:31,340 --> 00:02:32,220
Got it!

19
00:02:34,260 --> 00:02:36,760
Stay right there, ball!

20
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,260
He grabs a branch...

21
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:46,400
Gum-Gum...

22
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,940
It's the same as before.

23
00:02:47,940 --> 00:02:49,860
...Pistol!

24
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:51,480
To my left!

25
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,210
Don't be in such a rush!

26
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:11,500
Stay for a while!

27
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:31,690
Now then, where did
the other two go?

28
00:03:32,110 --> 00:03:35,150
I won't let a single one escape!

29
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,280
There you are!

30
00:03:41,450 --> 00:03:43,830
Hey! Do you see it, Usopp?!

31
00:03:52,340 --> 00:03:53,210
Found it!

32
00:03:53,210 --> 00:03:54,630
Give me directions!

33
00:03:54,630 --> 00:03:55,800
Straight ahead!

34
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:58,630
Climb up the tree after the next!

35
00:03:58,630 --> 00:04:00,720
You can jump onto it
from the branches!

36
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,890
Got it!

37
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:19,320
Yikes! It's him!

38
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,030
What's he up to?!

39
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:23,280
Go!

40
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,200
Look out, Sanji!

41
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,080
There's a ball headed your way!

42
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:29,500
What?! What's Luffy doing?!

43
00:04:39,510 --> 00:04:42,050
Surprise Billiard!

44
00:04:45,350 --> 00:04:46,640
Usopp!

45
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:50,560
He was aiming for me!

46
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:55,530
It's gonna explode!

47
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:58,360
"Pop"?!

48
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,490
Just a dud, huh?

49
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:08,660
Idiot!

50
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:13,500
You bastard!

51
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:16,670
Gum-Gum...

52
00:05:16,670 --> 00:05:19,260
Gatling!

53
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:27,430
Stop it, Luffy!

54
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:29,890
Don't hit those balls blindly!

55
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:36,360
What the...?! What's going on?!

56
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:37,860
It's over!

57
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:40,190
It's too late!

58
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:41,530
Look out!

59
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:43,530
They're coming from all directions!

60
00:05:45,530 --> 00:05:47,790
You people are fun!

61
00:05:56,210 --> 00:05:56,960
Spears!

62
00:05:56,960 --> 00:05:57,710
Crab!

63
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:03,630
Four at once!

64
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,520
For real?

65
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,480
More duds?

66
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,700
Hot!

67
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,820
Hot, hot, hot, hot, hot!

68
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:28,780
Water!

69
00:06:28,780 --> 00:06:29,790
Water, water, water!

70
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:31,200
Hot! Hot, hot, hot!

71
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,580
Hot, hot, hot, hot, hot!

72
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:36,080
The river!

73
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:42,340
That hurts!

74
00:06:50,470 --> 00:06:51,930
I fell through!

75
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,020
Luffy!

76
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:55,520
Don't land in the river below!

77
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,150
There might not be a bottom!

78
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:58,020
What?

79
00:07:08,990 --> 00:07:10,120
That was close!

80
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:26,180
Are you a moron?!

81
00:07:26,180 --> 00:07:27,550
Usopp Hammer!

82
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,640
Usopp Hammer!

83
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,890
Usopp Hammer!

84
00:07:29,890 --> 00:07:30,680
Rubber Band!

85
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,140
Usopp Hammer!

86
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:40,560
Yahoo!

87
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:44,490
Yahoo!

88
00:07:46,030 --> 00:07:48,410
Oh! I totally forgot about that!

89
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:50,700
Now's my chance to try it out!

90
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,420
Did you come up with
something, Usopp?!

91
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:02,550
I sure did!

92
00:08:02,550 --> 00:08:06,380
I'm known as the greatest
pirate inventor after all!

93
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:09,340
I'll show you my latest weapon!

94
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:12,140
Usopp...

95
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:14,850
Aah-eeh-aaaaaah!

96
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,350
What in the world?

97
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:18,100
Just wait and see!

98
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:21,310
There it is!

99
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:23,440
On the river straight ahead!

100
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,690
I can make it!

101
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:27,070
Set Up!

102
00:08:38,410 --> 00:08:40,210
What's he trying to do?

103
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,420
Alright!

104
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:48,010
Now it's just a straight line
to the Little Crow!

105
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:51,640
If it travels any further,
we won't be able to reach it!

106
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,970
I won't get another chance like this!

107
00:08:54,860 --> 00:08:55,470
Wow!

108
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:56,850
Not too shabby!

109
00:08:56,850 --> 00:08:58,560
Watch out for the balls!

110
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:00,600
I'm not gonna screw this one up!

111
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:03,980
You can call me the king of the jungle!

112
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,150
Here I go!

113
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:06,610
Usopp...

114
00:09:07,150 --> 00:09:12,110
Aah-eeh-ah-eeh-aaaaaah
-eeh-ah-eeh-aaaaah!

115
00:09:21,330 --> 00:09:23,750
What's wrong?! Just stick the landing!

116
00:09:24,130 --> 00:09:25,000
Yeah...

117
00:09:25,420 --> 00:09:27,130
about that...

118
00:09:27,130 --> 00:09:29,590
I forgot...

119
00:09:29,590 --> 00:09:35,600
that the rope is attached
to the belt, so I can't get loose!

120
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:43,480
Dammit! Dammit! Dammit!

121
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:46,270
Just... a bit... farther...

122
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:58,910
Yahoo!

123
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:00,160
Hey, Usopp!

124
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:01,910
You seem to be having fun too!

125
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,250
I need a word with you two.

126
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,720
Got it?

127
00:10:20,720 --> 00:10:24,900
If you follow my lead,
I'll forget what just happened.

128
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:26,900
Yes. I'm sorry.

129
00:10:26,900 --> 00:10:28,820
I'm very sorry.

130
00:10:28,820 --> 00:10:32,820
Forget about the boat for now.

131
00:10:33,450 --> 00:10:36,530
All three of us need
to attack him at once.

132
00:10:37,530 --> 00:10:39,790
I don't care if he is a priest.

133
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:43,330
Attacking him as a group
ought to put him down for good!

134
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:45,500
Beat me?!

135
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:54,800
Where'd he go?!

136
00:11:09,110 --> 00:11:10,190
Impact!

137
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:14,900
Sanji!

138
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,920
To live is to suffer.

139
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:28,830
Now then...

140
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:30,380
Only two left.

141
00:11:33,380 --> 00:11:34,880
A-All right!

142
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:37,010
Good thing this was here!

143
00:11:37,470 --> 00:11:38,340
Got it?

144
00:11:38,340 --> 00:11:40,970
I'll hold on to this whistle!

145
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:42,930
Any objections?!

146
00:11:42,930 --> 00:11:44,140
– Yes!
– Yes!

147
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:45,390
Yes! Yes!

148
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:47,560
How can you all say that?!

149
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:50,150
I'm the frailest girl here!

150
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:52,650
It's only natural that
I hold onto this whistle!

151
00:11:52,650 --> 00:11:53,860
I wanna blow it!

152
00:11:53,860 --> 00:11:58,610
You just wanna test
it out, Luffy! Forget it!

153
00:11:58,610 --> 00:12:01,660
I wanna call the old man right now!

154
00:12:01,660 --> 00:12:03,120
Let me hold on to it!

155
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,870
I'm the weakest!

156
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:08,000
You wish! I'm the weakest one of all!

157
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,880
What?! Quit screwing around!

158
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:12,130
I'm clearly the weakest here.

159
00:12:12,130 --> 00:12:14,380
No, I am! I'm the weakest!

160
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:18,260
Don't underestimate my hopelessness!

161
00:12:18,260 --> 00:12:19,970
I wanna blow the whistle!

162
00:12:19,970 --> 00:12:22,350
What a strange argument...
I wanna blow the whistle!

163
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,810
Let's do this, then!

164
00:12:27,810 --> 00:12:29,230
Center of the ship!

165
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:31,360
I'll hang it on the main mast,

166
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:35,190
so if anyone's in trouble,
they can grab and blow the whistle!

167
00:12:35,530 --> 00:12:36,820
Now it's fair!

168
00:12:36,820 --> 00:12:37,570
Alright.

169
00:12:37,570 --> 00:12:38,610
Got it.

170
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:40,660
Oh, also...

171
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:44,080
none of you have
permission to blow it!

172
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:46,660
But I wanna call the old man...

173
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:49,790
Blow it, and I'll kick
your ass off this planet!

174
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,630
– Yes, ma'am. We'll be careful.
– Yes ma'am. We'll be careful.

175
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:58,090
Now if anything happens,
the Sky Knight will come save me!

176
00:12:58,090 --> 00:13:01,680
But the whistle is a last resort!

177
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:03,550
Alright!

178
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:06,850
I'll do my very best
to watch over the ship!

179
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,570
What's that?

180
00:13:32,290 --> 00:13:33,540
Huh?

181
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:36,460
You're the only sacrifice I get to kill?

182
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:59,860
This year's pumpkins
grew exceptionally well.

183
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,490
Oh...

184
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:05,320
I cannot find the words
to express my gratitude.

185
00:14:05,740 --> 00:14:07,080
I'm sorry.

186
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:10,120
You ended up taking me in as well.

187
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:15,330
If they decide that your daughter
let those Straw Hat fellows escape,

188
00:14:15,330 --> 00:14:18,170
you'll be considered an accomplice.

189
00:14:18,170 --> 00:14:19,800
Your life is in danger.

190
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:22,840
This time is on the house...

191
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:27,600
Enel's mantra does not reach this far.

192
00:14:31,730 --> 00:14:33,890
How are things on Angel Island?

193
00:14:33,890 --> 00:14:35,100
Come again?

194
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,020
I'm referring to the crops.

195
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:38,980
Are they doing better this year?

196
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,570
Yes, they seem to be
coming along quite well.

197
00:14:41,570 --> 00:14:43,070
Is that so?

198
00:14:43,570 --> 00:14:44,700
I'm glad to hear it.

199
00:14:45,450 --> 00:14:49,580
This is juice made from
the pumpkins I grew in my field.

200
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:51,040
It's delicious.

201
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,040
Yes.

202
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,290
I'm sorry. Thank you.

203
00:14:55,170 --> 00:14:56,420
Conis.

204
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:58,250
Conis, come and try some.

205
00:15:05,510 --> 00:15:06,930
Young lady,

206
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:11,810
are you aware of those known as
"pirates" in the Blue Sea?

207
00:15:12,470 --> 00:15:13,390
No.

208
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:17,060
They are criminals who
travel on the ocean below.

209
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:25,030
Their ships all fly a black flag with a skull
that varies from crew to crew.

210
00:15:28,240 --> 00:15:32,540
Those Straw Hat fellows
are probably pirates too.

211
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,370
My word!

212
00:15:34,370 --> 00:15:37,460
Are you saying that they 
were criminals all along?

213
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:39,790
Well...

214
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:43,380
More accurately, they do not live
by the rules of the Blue Sea.

215
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:47,470
In any society, there are 
always those who don't fit in.

216
00:15:47,470 --> 00:15:50,470
How is it any different
from how you are now?

217
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,390
Who can say for certain

218
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:58,940
that society is right and 
that those who don't fit in are wrong?

219
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,860
It's not always so black and white.

220
00:16:01,770 --> 00:16:03,320
To put it in extreme terms,

221
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:09,660
a warhero from one era is
considered a murderer in another.

222
00:16:10,620 --> 00:16:13,990
I also have a pirate friend.

223
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:20,630
He came here when I was
still god over twenty years ago.

224
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:21,460
He was...

225
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:25,510
quite the compassionate
and pleasant fellow.

226
00:16:25,510 --> 00:16:27,930
It was a shame to say goodbye.

227
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:34,560
It may not seem like it at first glance,
but Skypiea is ravaged by endless war...

228
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:37,980
where the sky people...

229
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:44,150
and the Shandian guerrillas
battle continuously.

230
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:49,360
Even now, the Shandians
are still challenging Enel.

231
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:54,990
Your attempt to coexist with
the Shandians when you were god

232
00:16:54,990 --> 00:17:00,830
offered hope that the centuries-long
war would end peacefully.

233
00:17:01,210 --> 00:17:02,380
Yes...

234
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:08,670
I was very close to succeeding
before Enel usurped my title of god.

235
00:17:08,670 --> 00:17:10,090
I'm sorry.

236
00:17:10,090 --> 00:17:12,840
Everything worsened because of that.

237
00:17:12,840 --> 00:17:15,970
Wh-What are you saying?!
There's no need to apologize.

238
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:24,650
There's a legend in Skypiea
passed down from long ago:

239
00:17:25,070 --> 00:17:27,900
Once upon a time,

240
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:31,150
on the day that Upper Yard,
the sacred ground, was born,

241
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:35,780
the island's beautiful song
enveloped Skypiea.

242
00:17:36,290 --> 00:17:41,870
That's when the battle between
the Shandians and the sky people began...

243
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:45,380
as if that voice was a cue.

244
00:17:45,790 --> 00:17:54,050
So, when we hear the "song of
the island," this battle will end.

245
00:17:54,050 --> 00:17:56,890
The song of the island?

246
00:17:56,890 --> 00:17:58,020
That's right.

247
00:17:59,310 --> 00:18:02,390
The sacred ground will sing again...

248
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:06,020
someday, for sure.

249
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:19,410
What's the matter?

250
00:18:19,410 --> 00:18:21,790
Please look after this place.

251
00:18:21,790 --> 00:18:24,370
I've got a job to do. Let's go, Pierre!

252
00:18:57,660 --> 00:19:01,370
Father, this pumpkin juice is delicious!

253
00:19:01,870 --> 00:19:02,750
Yes.

254
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,620
I'm glad...

255
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:06,830
that you can enjoy it.

256
00:19:19,850 --> 00:19:21,350
Stop it!

257
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:23,350
Please stop it!

258
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:25,230
Don't harm the ship!

259
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:27,230
Anything but the ship!

260
00:19:32,150 --> 00:19:33,280
Dammit!

261
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:03,680
Dammit!

262
00:20:05,060 --> 00:20:06,770
Dammit!

263
00:20:06,770 --> 00:20:08,770
Stop it already!

264
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:11,060
I-I'm in charge of this ship!

265
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,650
They asked me to look after it!

266
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:19,110
Well...

267
00:20:19,570 --> 00:20:21,780
what should we do, Fuza?

268
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:25,080
Fuza
Nine-Meter Bird

269
00:20:25,080 --> 00:20:27,910
He says not to harm his friends.

270
00:20:27,910 --> 00:20:30,670
He says not to damage the ship.

271
00:20:30,670 --> 00:20:33,210
He says he doesn't want to die.

272
00:20:34,050 --> 00:20:35,590
What a dilemma.

273
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:40,970
"Sky Rider" Shura
Skypiea Priest

274
00:20:35,920 --> 00:20:38,800
Such a damn selfish animal!

275
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,970
He really irks me!

276
00:20:51,150 --> 00:20:52,770
Gan Fall...

277
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:58,030
How can a weak thing like you
cling to life so hopelessly?

278
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,110
Stop it!

279
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:03,200
That spear is burning everything!

280
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:10,370
Stop it!

281
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:11,790
Dammit!

282
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:15,710
You bastard!

283
00:21:17,170 --> 00:21:18,010
Wha...?

284
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:21,130
You intend to go on living...

285
00:21:22,090 --> 00:21:24,810
unprepared as you are
to make a sacrifice?

286
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,810
What is this guy?

287
00:21:26,810 --> 00:21:31,270
It's as if he can predict my moves.

288
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:37,780
For someone to live, another must die.

289
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:41,400
That is the rule of life.

290
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:48,120
Did you know that this
is a sacrificial altar?

291
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:50,040
Y-Yeah!

292
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,790
I heard something like that.

293
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:52,920
It's true.

294
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:58,300
The rest of your group
is desperately trying to get here.

295
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:05,550
On this island, there are four separate
areas that we priests govern.

